{
  "stem": "268.9",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I couldn't understand what's happening all around, all this madness?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Children are being slaughtered.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Have you ever answered that question for yourself?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Have I answered the question to myself?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Of course, as you-- as you get older-- it's still hard to-- to-- to reconcile when you see children being slaughtered.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I saw mothers throwing childre-- I was marching towards the station from the first assembly place.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I heard a thump.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And a lady was carrying something.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she said to the peasants who were standing, leaning over the fence.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She said, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She threw a bundle, and I heard a thump falling.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we were marching further.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she just looking back, and she threw her baby over the fence.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So it took an act of courage, and the toughness it took for a mother to throw-- what about my own mom, who kept saying, go, save yourself?",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And as I became a father myself, I keep thinking how courageous my mother was, and my dad, trying to protect us from all this madness, and how much courage it takes for a mother to part with her son, with her child who she loves so much, and say, go, you belong here now, here.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I kept clinging to her.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she pushed me away, as if she didn't want me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So as I became a parent, I kept-- so you see, your outlook, the way you see things as a young kid, and if you're in the middle of this, as I described in the beginning of my testimony about being in the center of the eye of the storm, it's hard sometimes, to see any reason.",
      "word_count": 57
    }
  ],
